Clicks says the executives and agency responsible for the ad should be named. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Unilever has so far failed to answer for the racist hair advert that's landed Clicks in trouble. Calls to the manufacturer of TRESemmé hair products have gone unanswered. READ: Clicks drops TRESemmé, senior executive resigns Clicks says the executives and agency responsible for the ad should be named. "This advert is not a Clicks advert, it is a TRESemmé advert," said Clicks Non-Executive Director, Nonkululeko Gobodo. "Unilever are the ones who must disclose the name of the agency and executives within Unilever who also approved this thing, no top executive at Clicks approved this thing because we didn’t commission it.”